### [Genesis Chapter 11](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#001.md)

[Genesis 11:1](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_001">gen 11:1</span></span>

one language

The history of Babel ("confusion") strikingly parallels that of the
professing Church.

\(1\) Unity ([Gen 11:1](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#001).md) -- the
Apostolic Church ([Act 4:32](../../../bib/kjv/act004.htm#032).md); ([Act
4:33](../../../bib/kjv/act004.htm#033).md).

\(2\) Ambition ([Gen 11:4](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#004).md) using
worldly, not spiritual means ([Gen
11:3](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#003).md) ending in a man-made unity --
the papacy;

\(3\) the confusion of tongues ([Gen
11:7](../../../bib/kjv/gen011.htm#007).md) -- Protestantism, with its
innumerable sects.

(See Scofield) - ([Isa 13:1](../../../bib/kjv/isa013.htm#001).md).

